            <h4>Symptoms</h4>
            <p>Symptoms of diabetes include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>being more thirsty than usual</li>
                <li>passing more urine</li>
                <li>feeling tired and lethargic</li>
                <li>slow-healing wounds</li>
                <li>itching and skin infections, particularly around the genitals</li>
                <li>blurred vision</li>
                <li>nausea and vomiting</li>
                <li>weight loss</li>
                <li>mood swings</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection-container">
            <h4>Treatment</h4>
            <p>Untreated diabetes can cause serious complications. With careful management of diet, exercise and medication consequences can be severely reduced or avoided all together.
                Diabetes@home is one way of managing diabetes and more information about how we can help can be found here.</p>
                
            <p>If you are worried about any of the above symptoms contact your local GP immediately and get in contact with them as soon as possible.</p>
